After Installing Node check for the version in terminal using (node -v)

Node Definiton: An asynchronus event driven javascript run time.

NODE REPL(Read Eval Print Loop)
It is a computer environment where user inputs are read and evaluated and then the results are returned to the user.
type node in your terminal to enter into repl, .exit to exit from it

to run Js file -> node index.js

npm init -> to intialise  NPM
npm install <something>   --> to install an npm package






